# A11yFocus

IDS A11yFocus component, captures the focus of the children in A11yFocus's child and can overwrite props on the child.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/a11yfocus
```

```tsx
import { A11yFocus } from '@ids-ts/a11yfocus';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `children` | `React.ReactElement | null` | No | - |
| `className` | `string` | No | ClassNames for the component |
| `onFocusClassName` | `string` | No | Merge classNames from classNames prop, onFocusClassName classNames, and child classNames |
| `passA11yFocusProp` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `style` | `React.CSSProperties` | No | Accepts an style object and passes it inline |
| `onA11yFocus` | `(isA11yFocus: boolean) => void` | No | onFocus fires on any focus event, while onA11yFocus only fires on tab key focus events |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface A11yFocusProps {
  /**
   * Children prop this only accepts 1 child
   *
   * @default null
   */
  children?: React.ReactElement | null;
  /** ClassNames for the component */
  className?: string;
  /** Merge classNames from classNames prop, onFocusClassName classNames, and child classNames */
  onFocusClassName?: string;
  /**
   * Pass a11yFocus prop only if passA11yFocusProp is set to true
   *
   * @default false
   */
  passA11yFocusProp?: boolean;
  /** Accepts an style object and passes it inline */
  style?: React.CSSProperties;
  /** onFocus fires on any focus event, while onA11yFocus only fires on tab key focus events */
  onA11yFocus?: (isA11yFocus: boolean) => void;
}
```

</details>

